Sal: (laughs)

00:20:01.302 --> 00:20:04.849
Sal: It's been very serendipitous.

00:20:04.849 --> 00:20:06.932
Sal: You know, it's been a combination.

00:20:06.932 --> 00:20:09.728
I actually think it's more of the latter.

00:20:09.728 --> 00:20:12.657
Obviously, all of us has spent
a lot of time in the system.

00:20:12.657 --> 00:20:16.532
I think the whole time,
anybody who knew me growing up,

00:20:16.532 --> 00:20:17.957
I mean, they knew that I was always like,

00:20:17.957 --> 00:20:20.655
Nina: Questioning, right.

00:20:20.655 --> 00:20:21.868
"Why can't I tutor?"

00:20:21.868 --> 00:20:23.325
I used to get reprimanded
for trying to tutor my-

00:20:23.325 --> 00:20:26.978
This is sort of been a
really positive interaction

00:20:26.978 --> 00:20:29.617
and so, this question, you go
to college and you're like,

00:20:29.617 --> 00:20:30.958
"People are sitting in this lecture hall,

00:20:30.958 --> 00:20:32.760
"is anything really happening in here?"

00:20:32.760 --> 00:20:34.921
It seems like all the learning is
happening under the cram session,

00:20:34.921 --> 00:20:37.702
three days before the final
