00:34:11.064 --> 00:34:13.104
and that made me feel good
because I was one of the people

00:34:13.104 --> 00:34:13.790
who were pre-exposed.

00:34:13.790 --> 00:34:15.541
It made me feel like I was meant to be.

00:34:15.541 --> 00:34:19.082
There wasn't luck but my
experience with my cousins,

00:34:19.082 --> 00:34:21.917
Nadia in particular, but other cousins
and then what we're seeing in schools.

00:34:21.917 --> 00:34:24.703
The schools that are
kind of transitioning to

00:34:24.703 --> 00:34:27.954
this type of a model where all the
students are learning at their own pace,

00:34:27.954 --> 00:34:30.640
building their foundations, we're seeing

00:34:31.393 --> 00:34:33.374
day five, yeah, some
kids have raced ahead.

00:34:33.374 --> 00:34:36.436
Those are the gifted kids and
some kids are falling behind

00:34:36.436 --> 00:34:38.836
like maybe they need to be
remediated and a traditional,

00:34:38.836 --> 00:34:41.352
how you would separate them and
you would actually tell these kids,

00:34:41.352 --> 00:34:42.299
"You're smart."

00:34:42.299 --> 00:34:44.736
You tell these kids either
explicitly or implicitly,

00:34:44.736 --> 00:34:47.318
"Hmm, you're not as smart."
but what we're saying is

00:34:47.318 --> 00:34:49.314
if you keep them together,
but you allow them

00:34:49.314 --> 00:34:50.936
to work at their own pace
so that they're engaged,

00:34:50.936 --> 00:34:52.448
