at age 16, you should learn
trigonometry and so on.

00:36:25.238 --> 00:36:27.154
You should learn physics, your
senior year in high school.

00:36:27.154 --> 00:36:28.697
You should learn, I mean
that's when it was decided

00:36:28.697 --> 00:36:30.332
and it hasn't changed since.

00:36:30.332 --> 00:36:31.494
I love all of those subjects.

00:36:31.494 --> 00:36:32.946
I think they're all fascinating

00:36:32.946 --> 00:36:35.443
but I think there are all these questions.

00:36:35.443 --> 00:36:37.787
Should there be more statistics?

00:36:37.787 --> 00:36:39.364
Statistics more valuable than calculus

00:36:39.364 --> 00:36:40.861
or at least as valuable.

00:36:40.861 --> 00:36:44.032
Should there be some
knowledge of economics?

00:36:44.032 --> 00:36:45.255
Who knows what it will be?

00:36:45.255 --> 00:36:47.113
I mean, it's for the society to decide

00:36:47.113 --> 00:36:48.864
but the general idea is

00:36:48.864 --> 00:36:53.452
at minimum, it should be rethought
within the last 120 years.

00:36:53.452 --> 00:36:55.196
There is grounds, the world has changed.

00:36:55.196 --> 00:36:57.636
We should think more about
what these subjects are.

00:36:57.636 --> 00:37:00.860
And even more, I think
and you alluded to this,

00:37:00.860 --> 00:37:03.850
should they even be divvied
up in these siloed subjects?

00:37:03.850 --> 00:37:05.524
These siloed subjects, these are,

00:37:05.524 --> 00:37:07.558
we're indoctrinated into
it, so it's hard for us

00:37:07.558 --> 00:37:09.372
to break our minds from it.

00:37:09.372 --> 00:37:11.323
This is the factory model.

00:37:11.323 --> 00:37:14.378
You're at this machine in the factory

00:37:14.378 --> 00:37:16.472
and so this is what will
be poured into the product.

00:37:16.472 --> 00:37:18.252
Okay, now you're gonna have
the paint applied to you.

00:37:18.252 --> 00:37:20.442
So now, you're gonna have
the chemistry applied to you.

00:37:20.442 --> 00:37:21.505
Now, you move on.

00:37:21.505 --> 00:37:23.727
And for some people that
might chip a little bit,

00:37:23.727 --> 00:37:24.527
that's fine.

00:37:24.527 --> 00:37:26.812
That'll be a cheaper product at the end

00:37:26.812 --> 00:37:28.241
but the reality is this,

00:37:28.241 --> 00:37:34.114
I mean chemistry is halfway
in between physics and biology

00:37:34.114 --> 00:37:37.945
and physics is halfway in between
chemistry and pure mathematics

00:37:37.945 --> 00:37:41.404
and all of them actually, have
an aspect of philosophy to them.

00:37:41.404 --> 00:37:43.693
All of them have an aspect
of aesthetics to them

00:37:43.693 --> 00:37:46.418
and whatever else and
riding can be critical

00:37:46.418 --> 00:37:49.535
and logical thinking
is across all program,

00:37:49.535 --> 00:37:51.777
you can have something like logic,

00:37:51.777 --> 00:37:52.861
which is across everything.

00:37:52.861 --> 00:37:57.134
And so, I think the
reality we're moving to is

00:37:57.134 --> 00:38:00.101
yes, you won't show competency in things.

00:38:00.101 --> 00:38:02.007
So, yeah I understand this domain well.

00:38:02.007 --> 00:38:05.258
So, you can go take an exam
and then renew that exam

00:38:05.258 --> 00:38:07.925
to show that, "Yes, I still
understand that topic."

00:38:07.925 --> 00:38:10.379
but while you're in school,
some might be preparation

00:38:10.379 --> 00:38:13.749
for that particular compentency
but most of the time,

00:38:13.749 --> 00:38:16.526
will be blending it
where you're not working

00:38:16.526 --> 00:38:17.947
to pass an assessment.

00:38:17.947 --> 00:38:19.412
You're working to create things

00:38:19.412 --> 00:38:21.070
and so, in the process of creating things,

00:38:21.070 --> 00:38:24.403
whether it might be a
novel or robot or business,

00:38:24.403 --> 00:38:25.903
you're integrating all of these things.

00:38:25.903 --> 00:38:27.367
I mean anyone who started a business,

00:38:27.367 --> 00:38:30.041
if it's like a tech
business, there's a comp,

00:38:30.041 --> 00:38:32.829
there's art design, there's technology,

00:38:32.829 --> 00:38:34.879
there's quantitative
thinking and there's writing

00:38:34.879 --> 00:38:37.212
and there's just human skills
and you need to integrate it.

00:38:37.212 --> 00:38:39.550
That's what actually
matters in the real world.

00:38:41.180 --> 00:38:45.133
When you break yourself from
this assembly line model,

00:38:45.133 --> 00:38:47.506
you give yourself the
freedom for people to pursue

00:38:47.506 --> 00:38:48.973
