what was happening there,

00:45:20.290 --> 00:45:22.681
is it's not something that's taught

00:45:22.681 --> 00:45:24.580
but it's something that can be untaught.

00:45:24.580 --> 00:45:28.955
It's not something that it's not,

00:45:28.955 --> 00:45:30.933
and it can be fostered
or it can be suppressed,

00:45:31.656 --> 00:45:32.972
both talent and creativity.

00:45:32.972 --> 00:45:35.012
And I actually think probably all,

00:45:35.012 --> 00:45:37.263
I think everyone is born with creativity.

00:45:37.263 --> 00:45:40.512
I mean there's not a
two-year-old on the planet,

00:45:40.512 --> 00:45:42.973
who, if you introduce a
new object into the room,

00:45:43.373 --> 00:45:46.433
will not walk up to that object
and manipulate it in every way,

00:45:46.433 --> 00:45:48.979
taste it, feel it, see what they
can do with it, pour something,

00:45:48.979 --> 00:45:50.479
There's not a two-year-old on the planet.

00:45:50.479 --> 00:45:51.679
There's not a five-year-old.

00:45:51.679 --> 00:45:53.281
Actually, most five-year-olds will still,

00:45:53.281 --> 00:45:55.014
a new object in the room,
they will engage with it,

00:45:55.014 --> 00:45:56.928
a new idea, they'll ask questions about it

00:45:56.928 --> 00:45:59.764
but then something happens
where they're taught

00:45:59.764 --> 00:46:01.124
to become more passive.

00:46:01.124 --> 00:46:02.835
To some degree, they are in an environment

00:46:02.835 --> 00:46:05.497
where questioning is not always cool.

00:46:06.035 --> 00:46:08.985
