00:46:08.985 --> 00:46:10.981
whether it's soccer practice or homework

00:46:10.981 --> 00:46:14.150
that there's no time for them to
kind of just think about something.

00:46:14.150 --> 00:46:15.324
The class is moving on.

00:46:15.324 --> 00:46:17.717
They can't think about, "Wait,
why am I carrying the one?

00:46:17.717 --> 00:46:20.002
"Why does that make sense? It
seems just like a formula to me."

00:46:20.002 --> 00:46:21.417
They don't have time
for that type of stuff

00:46:21.417 --> 00:46:25.495
and so, all of these
things, fall from this idea

00:46:25.495 --> 00:46:27.338
of just breaking from this Prussian model,

00:46:27.338 --> 00:46:29.384
breaking from this one
pace fits the lecture.

00:46:29.384 --> 00:46:30.852
As soon as you take that out,

00:46:30.852 --> 00:46:32.007
now, all of a sudden,
you can start saying,

00:46:32.007 --> 00:46:34.398
"Hey, why we can't we let a student ..."

