00:46:51.016 --> 00:46:54.758
I have, I quote, an admissions
officer in the book talked

00:46:54.758 --> 00:46:57.287
about she was interviewing
a bunch of people

00:46:57.287 --> 00:46:59.237
who are coming to a very
elite college and said,

00:46:59.237 --> 00:47:01.592
"What do you daydream
about?" and one student said,

00:47:01.592 --> 00:47:02.709
"We don't daydream about anything

00:47:02.709 --> 00:47:04.367
"because it doesn't help
us to get into college."

00:47:05.043 --> 00:47:08.499
And it's tragic for that child
but it's tragic for society

00:47:08.499 --> 00:47:12.257
because it's those daydreams
that eventually lead to actual,

00:47:12.257 --> 00:47:15.175
I'll tell you know, Khan
Academy exist to a large degree

00:47:15.175 --> 00:47:19.305
because my boss at the hedge
fund, a very nontraditional

00:47:19.305 --> 00:47:22.640
for that field, had a
strong belief in life, work

00:47:22.640 --> 00:47:27.011
in balance and so, I had time to
daydream about the Khan Academy.

00:47:27.011 --> 00:47:28.798
I had time.

