00:49:58.536 --> 00:50:01.137
I think they should set an example.

00:50:01.137 --> 00:50:03.963
It's become too, it's too
easy now in our society

00:50:03.963 --> 00:50:06.109
for people to say, "Oh,
I'm not good at math."

00:50:06.109 --> 00:50:07.963
And they'll say it out
loud like 6th grade math.

00:50:07.963 --> 00:50:09.936
"Oh, I don't know. That's
math. I don't understand it."

00:50:09.936 --> 00:50:12.309
No one will say, "Oh, I can't
read at a 6th grade level."

00:50:12.309 --> 00:50:14.023
or, "I can barely write."

00:50:14.023 --> 00:50:16.859
No one says that but people say,
you'll hear politicians say that.

00:50:16.859 --> 00:50:18.366
You'll hear CEOs say that.

00:50:18.366 --> 00:50:20.492
You'll hear people in the press say that

00:50:20.492 --> 00:50:22.782
and I think that messaging should change

00:50:22.782 --> 00:50:24.574
and frankly, the only
way that it could change,

00:50:24.574 --> 00:50:26.004
is if they directly engage with it.

00:50:26.004 --> 00:50:29.343
I mean it's shocking how many people
are engaged in education policy,

00:50:30.189 --> 00:50:31.748
where they don't know the
subject matter themselves.

00:50:31.748 --> 00:50:33.209
They're like, "Oh, I'm
not good at math but

00:50:33.209 --> 00:50:35.506
"this is how we should
test math teachers."

00:50:35.506 --> 00:50:36.874
It's like, that's crazy.

00:50:36.874 --> 00:50:40.125
You yourself should engage in the
content or get a depth in the content

00:50:40.125 --> 00:50:41.876
and that'll be a huge signal to society

00:50:41.876 --> 00:50:44.265
and I think it also help inform policy

00:50:44.265 --> 00:50:45.978
and I think the more they do that,

00:50:45.978 --> 00:50:48.387
they'll realize that it's a
lot less about taught down,

00:50:48.387 --> 00:50:50.351
a lot less about the controls.

00:50:50.351 --> 00:50:53.209
The controls that they do, every
iteration of ed reforms is just

00:50:53.209 --> 00:50:56.399
about more controls on
teachers and it might

00:50:56.968 --> 00:51:03.365
de-risk some of the weaker players
but it also handicaps all the rest

00:51:03.365 --> 00:51:06.574
and so it kind of gets into
this culture of everyone getting

00:51:07.312 --> 00:51:09.825
to mediocre and what we really
need to do is go the other way.

00:51:09.825 --> 00:51:11.503
Be much more grassroots.

00:51:11.503 --> 00:51:13.708
What I point on this book,
that's an American thing

00:51:13.708 --> 00:51:16.824
that we're a country that's
focused on creativity,

00:51:16.824 --> 00:51:18.901
we're a country that's focused
on people taking ownership

00:51:18.901 --> 00:51:21.821
over their lives but our school
system is a Prussian one.

00:51:22.282 --> 00:51:24.816
One that's about passivity.

00:51:24.816 --> 00:51:28.434
One that's about authority and
everything about this book is,

00:51:28.434 --> 00:51:31.024
let's make our school
system more American.

